Fifteen Wits University students took on a 1,000km walk and raised R7 million for those who could not afford tuition fees. CAPE TOWN - At least 10 talented young people will have a shot at tertiary education next year thanks to an epic pilgrimage across South Africa.Fifteen Wits University students took on a 1,000km walk to raise funds for those who could not afford tuition fees. They managed to raise R7 million and doubtless more than a couple of blisters. Feet4Fees member Thabo Thulare said: It s a national bursary administrator which means wherever you are in South Africa, you are able to access the money as long as you can apply and meet the requirements that study trust will set forward. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)